## Hooks 

### Four Hook Types
| Hook | Level | Runs |
|---|---|---|
| `on-run-start` | Pipeline | Once before entire run |
| `on-run-end` | Pipeline | Once after entire run |
| `pre-hook` | Model | Before each model |
| `post-hook` | Model | After each model |
| Global `+post-hook` | Model (defined globally) | After every model — one definition |

### dbt_project.yml Hook Config
```yaml
on-run-start:
  - "create table if not exists dbt_db.raw.dbt_run_log (run_id varchar, model_name varchar, status varchar, run_at timestamp)"
  - "insert into dbt_db.raw.dbt_run_log values ('{{ invocation_id }}', 'PIPELINE', 'started', current_timestamp())"

on-run-end:
  - "insert into dbt_db.raw.dbt_run_log values ('{{ invocation_id }}', 'PIPELINE', 'completed', current_timestamp())"

models:
  dbt_learning:
    +post-hook:
      - "insert into dbt_db.raw.dbt_run_log values ('{{ invocation_id }}', '{{ this.name }}', 'success', current_timestamp())"
```

### Model-level Hook
```sql
{{ config(
    materialized='table',
    pre_hook="create or replace temp table temp_active_customers as select customer_id from dbt_db.raw_staging.stg_customers where status = 'active'",
    post_hook="grant select on {{ this }} to role sysadmin"
) }}
```

### Hook Variables
| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `{{ this }}` | Full table reference |
| `{{ this.name }}` | Model name only |
| `{{ this.schema }}` | Schema name only |
| `{{ invocation_id }}` | Unique ID for current dbt run |

### What Your Run Log Shows
```
invocation_id | model_name            | status    | run_at
abc123        | PIPELINE              | started   | 2024-01-01 02:00:00
abc123        | stg_customers         | success   | 2024-01-01 02:00:05
abc123        | mart_customer_summary | success   | 2024-01-01 02:00:11
abc123        | PIPELINE              | completed | 2024-01-01 02:00:12
```

### Checking Pre-hook Temp Table
Temp tables exist only during the session — verify via:
1. `dbt run --debug` — look for pre-hook SQL in output
2. Snowflake Query History → filter by `dbt_wh` → look for `CREATE OR REPLACE TEMP TABLE`
3. Add post-hook that counts rows and writes to log table

### Key Nuances
- `on-run-start/end` are already global — define once in `dbt_project.yml`
- `{{ this }}` only available in model-level hooks — not `on-run-start/end`
- Global `+post-hook` = per model logging without touching individual files
- Failed hooks don't automatically fail the model
- Hooks run in array order — list multiple as array

